options.content: Ethereum “full nodes” that Splunk is running to connect to the xDai sidechain network. These nodes connect to a random set of peers to download a copy of the blockchain. These nodes also help distribute copies of the blockchain to its peers. We use them to gather analytics and monitor our transactions in order to ensure the network is behaving as we expect.
The Cloudfront CDN serves all the front end assets (images, CSS, JS) for the Buttercup Bucks mobile wallet.
This is an AWS lambda function that receives telemetry data from the Buttercup Bucks mobile wallet and forwards it to the Splunk instance so we can monitor usage and performance.
This AWS lambda function authenticates your .conf19 user credentials and loads the Buttercup Bucks wallet with your private key.

Cryptocurrency addresses are public / private keypairs. This means that if the private key is ever lost, all balance associated with the public address is also unrecoverable. In order to make the user experience more seamless for Buttercup Bucks, we keep a copy of private keys for each user in an RDS database so they can be recovered. Cryptocurrency is permissionless! You can move your tokens to your own address that we don’t have the private key for at your own risk! The pony.cash wallet does not support this in the UI, but the crypto-saavy can figure out a way....
Rainfocus is the conference registration API. It is used by the Auth Lambda (D) to authenticate your mobile wallet.

Pony.cash is a mobile wallet that stores your private key in order to sign and send transactions of Buttercup Bucks with a slick user interface. It is similar to a regular mobile app, except that instead of only being able to talk to one server, it can talk to any blockchain node to send and receive transactions. This is how a decentralized web 3.0 applications will work.

This is a list of the validators on the public xDai blockchain network. These nodes are responsible for producing and signing blocks -- they provide a similar service to the miners on the Bitcoin network. All your transactions must be approved by 2/3rds of these validators in order to be finalized on the xDai network. Unlike Bitcoin, the validators are required to be publicly known and authenticated in this network, this enables cheaper and faster transactions but less decentralization.

A typical credit card transaction fee is $0.10 plus 1.5% of the transaction value. On this blockchain network there is no central authority that collects the fees, instead the nodes are incentivized to validate transactions in return for a small payment. This shows a comparison of what the fees are on this network in USD vs what it would cost on a traditional payment network.

options.query:
index="xdainew" sourcetype=transaction* 
| timechart partial=f span=5m count 
| fields count _time

index="xdainew" sourcetype=transaction:event name=TransferWithData address=0x4b78a47532d9e966574d30189b3de734a232a78a 
| timechart count

| stats count 
| eval count=90

| stats count
| eval count="100"

index=xdainew sourcetype=block 
| eventstats max(number) as maxBlock 
| eval miner=if(miner="0x657eA4A9572DfdBFd95899eAdA0f6197211527BE","Burner Wallet",if(miner="0x9e41BA620FebA8198369c26351063B26eC5b7C9E","MakerDAO",if(miner="0xA13D45301207711B7C0328c6b2b64862abFe9b7a","Protofire",if(miner="0x9233042B8E9E03D5DC6454BBBe5aee83818fF103","POA Network",if(miner="0xb76756f95A9fB6ff9ad3E6cb41b734c1bd805103","Portis",if(miner="0x6dC0c0be4c8B2dFE750156dc7d59FaABFb5B923D","Giveth",if(miner="0x657E832b1a67CDEF9e117aFd2F419387259Fa93e","Syncnode S.R.L",if(miner="0xa1c3Eb21cD44F0433c6be936AD84D20b70B564D3","MetaCartel",if(miner="0x10AaE121b3c62F3DAfec9cC46C27b4c1dfe4A835","Lab10 Collective",if(miner="0xA84713b6241260B3CaA2c4be00fF62b89C4315c2","Ztake.org","Unknown"))))))))))  
| stats dc(transactions{}) AS Txns sparkline(dc(transactions{})) AS "Txn History" count AS Events latest(number) AS "Last Block" by miner maxBlock 
| eval "Blocks Behind"=maxBlock-'Last Block' 
| rename miner AS Miner maxBlock AS "Max Block"
| table Miner Txns "Txn History" "Blocks Behind" "Last Block" 
| rename "Last Block" AS "L_Block" "Blocks Behind" AS Behind Miner AS Validator

| stats count
| eval count="NORMAL"

| tstats avg(CloudFront_Access_Log.time_taken) as time_taken FROM datamodel=CloudFront_Access_Log where (CloudFront_Access_Log.cs_host="*") AND ((*)) by CloudFront_Access_Log.cs_host CloudFront_Access_Log.edge_location_name CloudFront_Access_Log.cs_uri_stem _time 
| timechart partial=f span=3m avg(time_taken) as duration 
| eval duration=round(duration,0) 
| fillnull value=1 
| fields duration _time

index="pony*" 
| stats dc(clientid) as users

index="ponycashauth" (source="source=app:telemetry" OR source="wallet-api-access") durationMS=* 
| timechart span=2m partial=f avg(durationMS) as latency 
| fields latency _time 
| search latency>0

index=xdainew sourcetype=block 
| stats latest(number) as xdaiBlockNum 
| appendcols 
    [| geth blockNumber host=https://pony-cash.infura.io
    | rename blockNumber AS InfuraBlockNum 
    | fields InfuraBlockNum] 
| eval dif=InfuraBlockNum-xdaiBlockNum 
| fields dif

index="pony*" 
| timechart count

index="ponycashauth" (source=wallet-api-access status!=200) 
| stats count 
| appendcols 
    [ search index="ponycashauth" (source="source=app:telemetry" OR source="wallet-api-access") durationMS=* 
    | stats avg(durationMS) as latency 
    | fields latency] 
| eval health=if(count=0 AND latency<500,100,if(count<3 AND latency<500,95,if(count<5 AND latency<1000,90,80))) 
| fields health

index="ponycashauth" (source=wallet-api-access status!=200) 
| stats count

`aws-cloudwatch-rds( (aws_account_id="414345301310") , (region="*"))` (metric_dimensions="DBInstanceIdentifier=[*]") metric_name="CPUUtilization" 
| `aws-cloudwatch-dimension-rex("DBInstanceIdentifier", "Instance")` 
| stats avg(Average) as valueCPU by Instance 
| search Instance="pony-cash-prod" 
| appendcols 
    [ search `aws-cloudwatch-rds( (aws_account_id="414345301310") , (region="*"))` (metric_dimensions="DBInstanceIdentifier=[*]") metric_name="FreeableMemory" 
    | `aws-cloudwatch-dimension-rex("DBInstanceIdentifier", "Instance")` 
    | stats avg(Average) as valueFreeMEM by Instance 
    | eval valueFreeMEM=round(valueFreeMEM/1024/1024,2) 
    | search Instance="pony-cash-prod"] 
| eval health=if(valueCPU<30 AND valueFreeMEM>2000,"100",if(valueCPU<50 AND valueFreeMEM>1500,"80","50")) 
| fields health

| mstats count prestats=true WHERE metric_name="memory.free" AND index="em_metrics" AND host="ubuntu" span=5m BY host 
| timechart partial=f count span=5m agg=max limit=5 useother=false BY host 
| fields - _span 
| sort - _time 
| head 1 
| appendcols 
    [| makeresults 
    | eval isdown="DOWN"] 
| eval up_down=if(ubuntu>0,"UP",isdown) 
| fields up_down

| mstats count prestats=true WHERE metric_name="memory.free" AND index="em_metrics" AND host="ip-172-31-11-176" span=5m BY host 
| timechart partial=f count span=5m agg=max limit=5 useother=false BY host 
| fields - _span 
| sort - _time 
| head 1 
| rename "ip-172-31-11-176" AS xdai_node1 
| appendcols 
    [| makeresults 
    | eval isdown="DOWN"] 
| eval up_down=if(xdai_node1>0,"UP",isdown)
| fields up_down

`aws-cloudwatch-lambda( (aws_account_id="*") , (region="*"))` 
| where Average>0 
| stats avg(Average) as avg by metric_dimensions metric_name _time 
| `aws-cloudwatch-dimension-rex("FunctionName", "FunctionName")` 
| search metric_name=Duration 
| search FunctionName="us-east-1.lmoqt2c-fcguqyq"
| timechart partial=f span=2m avg(avg) as value 
|  fields value _time 
| search value>0

`aws-cloudwatch-lambda( (aws_account_id="*") , (region="*"))` 
| where Average>0 
| stats avg(Average) as avg by metric_dimensions metric_name _time 
| `aws-cloudwatch-dimension-rex("FunctionName", "FunctionName")` 
| search metric_name=Duration 
| search FunctionName="us-east-1.lmoqt2c-58joc5d"
| timechart partial=f span=5m avg(avg) as value 
|  fields value _time 
| search value>0

| stats count 
| eval count=1

| mstats count prestats=true WHERE metric_name="memory.free" AND index="em_metrics" AND host="ip-172-31-11-176" span=5m BY host 
| timechart partial=f count span=5m agg=max limit=5 useother=false BY host 
| fields - _span 
| sort - _time 
| head 1 
| rename "ip-172-31-11-176" AS xdai_node1 
| appendcols 
    [| makeresults 
    | eval isdown="DOWN"] 
| eval up_down=if(xdai_node1>0,"UP",isdown)
| fields up_down

index="xdainew" sourcetype=transaction to=0x4B78a47532D9e966574D30189B3dE734A232A78a (method.name=transferWithData OR method.name=transfer) status=success
| dedup hash  
| eval value=`fromBcbWei('method.args._value')` 
|stats sum(value) AS total dc(hash) as num_transactions sum(gas) AS gas
| eval transaction_fee=total*0.015+num_transactions*0.029, gas_cost=gas/1000000000
| fields transaction_fee

index="xdainew" sourcetype=transaction to=0x4B78a47532D9e966574D30189B3dE734A232A78a (method.name=transferWithData OR method.name=transfer) status=success
| dedup hash  
| eval value=`fromBcbWei('method.args._value')` 
|stats sum(value) AS total dc(hash) as num_transactions sum(gas) AS gas
| eval transaction_fee=total*0.015+num_transactions*0.029, gas_cost=gas/1000000000
| fields gas_cost

index="xdainew" sourcetype=transaction to=0x4B78a47532D9e966574D30189B3dE734A232A78a (method.name=transferWithData OR method.name=transfer) status=success 
| dedup hash 
| eval value=`fromBcbWei('method.args._value')` 
| stats sum(value) AS total dc(hash) as num_transactions sum(gas) AS gas 
| eval transaction_fee=total*0.015+num_transactions*0.029, gas_cost=gas/1000000000 
| fields transaction_fee gas_cost 
| eval ratio=(transaction_fee/gas_cost) 
| fields ratio
